			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Do you have scanline clipping turned off?  The NES renders 240 scanlines, but when emulating NTSC, most emulators chop off the top and bottom 8 scanlines (only rendering 224 scanlines) since the top and bottom are chopped off on most NTSC displays.
<br />
<br />If one emu is chopping off the top 8 lines, and another isn't, it may appear that one is rendering the image lower than the other -- when it really isn't.  One just isn't showing the whole picture.
<br />
<br />Your code is drawing to ppu$2020, so <strong>without</strong> clipping, this will start drawing 8 pixels down from the top of ths screen.  With clipping it will start at the very top of the screen.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
